The paper deals with a problem in probability theory and its application to dimensionality reduction, which suggests that it could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) categories. The use of quantization and distortion levels also suggests a connection to Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Numerical Analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the mention of quasi-isometric embeddings and Lipschitz isometric embeddings suggests a connection to Computational Complexity (cs.CC).
